# JMeter Load Test Script Runbook (Four Monolith Applications)

## 0. Always restart the corresponding Docker images before each run

1. Stop and restart the corresponding monolith application containers (AcmeAir / JPetStore / DayTrader / Plants) to ensure a clean state.
2. Wait until the application is fully started (homepage is accessible), then run the JMeter scripts.

# Enter the directory that contains docker-compose.yml
cd D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\docker

# Stop and remove all containers
docker compose down

# Start all services (run in background)
docker compose up -d

# Check status
docker compose ps

# View logs for a single container (e.g., JPetStore)
docker logs jpetstore

## 1. Prerequisites

1. JMeter 5.6.3 is installed, e.g., `D:\apache-jmeter-5.6.3`.
2. The current working directory is the project root: `D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction`.
3. The JMeter test plans (.jmx) in this repository are archived under: `scripts\jmeter\`.
4. In each `.jmx`, ensure the target URL and local ports match your environment (e.g., JPetStore uses `http://localhost:8083/jpetstore`).

## 2. Run the four JMeter scripts in PowerShell

Run the following commands **in PowerShell** in order (note: use backtick ` as the line continuation character).

> Tip: you can `cd D:\apache-jmeter-5.6.3\bin` first and then reference the `.jmx` files via relative paths.

### 2.1 JPetStore

cd D:\apache-jmeter-5.6.3\bin

```powershell
D:\apache-jmeter-5.6.3\bin\jmeter.bat -n `
  -t "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\scripts\jmeter\jpetstore.jmx" `
  -l "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\results\jmeter\jpetstore_results.jtl" `
  -j "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\results\jmeter\jpetstore_jmeter.log" `

```

### 2.2 Plants

```powershell
D:\apache-jmeter-5.6.3\bin\jmeter.bat -n `
  -t "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\scripts\jmeter\plants.jmx" `
  -l "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\results\jmeter\plants_results.jtl" `
  -j "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\results\jmeter\plants_jmeter.log" `

```

### 2.3 DayTrader

```powershell
D:\apache-jmeter-5.6.3\bin\jmeter.bat -n `
  -t "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\scripts\jmeter\daytrader.jmx" `
  -l "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\results\jmeter\daytrader_results.jtl" `
  -j "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\results\jmeter\daytrader_jmeter.log" `

```

### 2.4 AcmeAir

```powershell
D:\apache-jmeter-5.6.3\bin\jmeter.bat -n `
  -t "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\scripts\jmeter\acmeair1.jmx" `
  -l "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\results\jmeter\acmeair1_results.jtl" `
  -j "D:\multimodal_microservice_extraction\results\jmeter\acmeair1_jmeter.log" `

```

## 3. Output file conventions

- JTL: `results/jmeter/<system>_results.jtl`
- JMeter log: `results/jmeter/<system>_jmeter.log`
- HTML report: `results/jmeter/<system>_html_report/`

Where `<system> ∈ {acmeair, jpetstore, daytrader, plants}`.